Pico 3 active firmware: painting rotation puzzle.

This folder is the active Pico 3 project. The old TV wall trigger code is archived in:

../../pico6-unused-future-puzzles/unused-future-puzzles/

Hardware:
- GPIO 15: sensor white/signal output, using the Pico internal pull-up
- 3V3: sensor red/VCC
- GND: sensor black/GND

Main topics:
- Publishes escape/pico3/painting_rotation_complete when the active sensor is freshly triggered
- Subscribes escape/cmd/all/status_request
- Subscribes escape/cmd/all/reset_puzzle

The sensor is always active from startup/reset. As soon as the input reads LOW,
the Pico publishes the painting rotation event and the Raspberry Pi plays
assets/audio/crashing_plates.m4a.

The event publishes once when the magnet pulls the sensor input LOW, then
re-arms after the input returns HIGH.
